      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Graph-based agents represent control flow as an explicit directed graph of node functions sharing a typed state. Nodes read state and return partial updates; conditional edges select the next node at runtime. LangGraph handles state merging, graph validation, and optional checkpointing. Use the graph model when your workflow has loops, branches, or long-running sessions that need to survive restarts — fall back to LCEL chains for simple linear pipelines where the overhead of a full graph is not justified."
          }
        ]
